libxc
------------------------------------------
libxc is a library of exchange and correlation functionals. Its purpose is to
be used in codes that implement density-functional theory. For the moment, the
library includes most of the local density approximations (LDAs), generalized
density approximation (GGAs), and meta-GGAs. The library provides values for
the energy density and its 1st, 2nd, and (for the LDAs) 3rd derivatives.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.4-1
  libgfortran5-9.3.0-2
  libxc-devel-5.0.0-1bl1
  libxc9-5.0.0-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cmake-3.14.5-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-9.3.0-2
  gcc-fortran-9.3.0-2
  libtool-2.4.6-7
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://tddft.org/programs/libxc/

Canonical download:
  https://gitlab.com/libxc/libxc/-/archive/5.0.0/libxc-5.0.0.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libxc-5.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libxc-5.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libxc-5.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libxc-5.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libxc9-5.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libxc-devel-5.0.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libxc)
  /usr/bin/xc-info.exe
  /usr/bin/xc-threshold.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libxc.README
  /usr/share/doc/libxc/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libxc/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libxc/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libxc/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/libxc/README
  /usr/share/doc/libxc/TODO
  /usr/share/doc/libxc/readme.md

(libxc9)
  /usr/bin/cygxc-9.dll
  /usr/bin/cygxcf90-9.dll

(libxc-devel)
  /usr/include/libxc.bib
  /usr/include/xc.h
  /usr/include/xc_f90_lib_m.mod
  /usr/include/xc_funcs.h
  /usr/include/xc_funcs_removed.h
  /usr/include/xc_funcs_worker.h
  /usr/include/xc_version.h
  /usr/lib/libxc.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libxcf90.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libxc.pc
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libxcf03.pc
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libxcf90.pc

